tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE impact_of_gentrification (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    city VARCHAR(50),
    neighborhood VARCHAR(50),
    housing_price DECIMAL(10, 2),
    gentrification_level INT
);

CREATE TABLE housing_prices (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    city VARCHAR(255),
    neighborhood VARCHAR(255),
    year INT,
    property_type VARCHAR(50),
    price DECIMAL(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE gentrification (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    city VARCHAR(255),
    neighborhood VARCHAR(255),
    gentrification_year INT,
    impact_rating INT
);

CREATE TABLE demographics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    city VARCHAR(255),
    neighborhood VARCHAR(255),
    population INT,
    median_income DECIMAL(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE economic_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    location VARCHAR(255),
    year INT,
    income DECIMAL(10, 2),
    employment_rate DECIMAL(5, 2)
);

CREATE TABLE housing_prices (
    property_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    area_id INT NOT NULL,
    property_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    price DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,
    year_built INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (area_id) REFERENCES urban_areas(area_id)
);

CREATE TABLE gentrification_factors (
    factor_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    area_id INT NOT NULL,
    factor_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    factor_description TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (area_id) REFERENCES urban_areas(area_id)
);

CREATE TABLE gentrification_impact (
    impact_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    area_id INT NOT NULL,
    impact_year INT NOT NULL,
    impact_description TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (area_id) REFERENCES urban_areas(area_id)
);
